Task: React (TypeScript) Project Using FreeTestAPI

You are tasked with developing a React (TypeScript) application that interacts with the FreeTestAPI Movies API. Your goal is to create a dynamic and user-friendly interface that displays movie data efficiently.

Requirements:

Movie List Page:
Fetch and display a list of movies from https://freetestapi.com/api/v1/movies.
Show essential details such as title, year, genre, rating, and poster.
Search Functionality:
Implement a search bar to filter movies by title using search query api “https://freetestapi.com/api/v1/movies?search=[query]”
Display results dynamically as the user types.
Sorting Feature:
Allow users to sort movies by title, year, or rating in ascending/descending order using sort api “https://freetestapi.com/api/v1/movies?sort=name&order=desc”
Movie Details Page:
When a user clicks on a movie, navigate to a detailed view page.
Fetch movie details using https://freetestapi.com/api/v1/movies/{id}.
Display additional information like plot, director, actors, runtime, awards, and box office earnings.
Technology Stack:

React (TypeScript)
React Router for navigation
Axios or Fetch API for API requests
Deliverables:

A GitHub repository with your project code